    "created_at": "2014-05-20T15:47:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-05-20T15:47:56Z",
    "body": "File paths passed to Node's APIs are treated as real file system paths, instead of the relative paths used by HTML. So `/photo.jpg` in your case represents the `photo.jpg` under the `/`, e.g. the file system's root.\n"
  },
